<subSubSection id="C35B708FB601FFC2FF5DB62EFB58F8E8" box="[198,1223,1804,1830]" pageId="1" pageNumber="36" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BFE2304B601FFC2FF5DB62EFB58F8E8" blockId="1.[151,1437,589,2030]" box="[198,1223,1804,1830]" pageId="1" pageNumber="36">
<emphasis id="B935FF16B601FFC2FF5DB62EFECCF8E8" bold="true" box="[198,339,1804,1830]" pageId="1" pageNumber="36">Etymology.</emphasis>
This species epithet honors the collector of the specimens, Prof. Wu Hong.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C35B708FB601FFC1FF5DB616FA04FF12" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="37" pageId="1" pageNumber="36" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BFE2304B601FFC1FF5DB616FA04FF12" blockId="1.[151,1437,589,2030]" lastBlockId="2.[151,1436,152,220]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="37" pageId="1" pageNumber="36">
<emphasis id="B935FF16B601FFC2FF5DB616FED9F880" bold="true" box="[198,326,1844,1870]" pageId="1" pageNumber="36">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species is similar to the Neotropical species 
<taxonomicName id="4C415887B601FFC2FC06B616FBEAF880" authority="Edwards" authorityName="Edwards" box="[925,1141,1844,1870]" class="Insecta" family="Keroplatidae" genus="Platyroptilon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zernyi">
<emphasis id="B935FF16B601FFC2FC06B616FB9BF883" box="[925,1028,1844,1869]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="36">P. zernyi</emphasis>
Edwards
</taxonomicName>
, in having 
<number id="3D893123B601FFC2FB67B616FA86F880" box="[1276,1305,1844,1870]" pageId="1" pageNumber="36" value="14.0">14</number>
flagellomeres, but it is easily distinguished by the apical two flagellomeres being pale yellow (these flagellomeres are brown in 
<emphasis id="B935FF16B601FFC2FE9DB6A6FEF9F853" box="[262,358,1924,1949]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="36">P. z e r n y i</emphasis>
) and the distinct difference between the shape of their gonostylus. Having compared 
<emphasis id="B935FF16B601FFC2FAD5B6A6FA0EF853" box="[1358,1425,1924,1949]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="36">P. w u i</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis id="B935FF16B601FFC2FF0CB68EFF45F808" bold="true" box="[151,218,1964,1990]" pageId="1" pageNumber="36">n. sp.</emphasis>
with the Oriental species 
<taxonomicName id="4C415887B601FFC2FD96B68EFC94F808" authority="Matile" authorityName="Matile" box="[525,779,1964,1990]" class="Insecta" family="Keroplatidae" genus="Platyroptilon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kirkspriggsi">
<emphasis id="B935FF16B601FFC2FD96B68EFD28F80B" box="[525,695,1964,1989]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="36">P. kirkspriggsi</emphasis>
Matile
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis id="B935FF16B601FFC2FCDEB68EFC29F80B" box="[837,950,1964,1989]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="36">P. s c u r ro r</emphasis>
Matile, we have found that the new species differs in having 
<number id="3D893123B601FFC2FE38B6F6FE5FF820" box="[419,448,2004,2030]" pageId="1" pageNumber="36" value="14.0">14</number>
flagellomeres (only 
<number id="3D893123B601FFC2FD25B6F6FD44F820" box="[702,731,2004,2030]" pageId="1" pageNumber="36" value="12.0">12</number>
flagellomeres in the two mentioned species), radiomedial fusion 
<number id="3D893123B602FFC1FF72B1BAFE92FF7C" box="[233,269,152,178]" pageId="2" pageNumber="37" value="1.3">1.3</number>
x length of petiole of M (
<number id="3D893123B602FFC1FDA5B1BAFDFBFF7C" box="[574,612,152,178]" pageId="2" pageNumber="37" value="0.5">0.5</number>
x in 
<taxonomicName id="4C415887B602FFC1FD07B1BAFCD9FF7F" box="[668,838,152,177]" class="Insecta" family="Keroplatidae" genus="Platyroptilon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kirkspriggsi">
<emphasis id="B935FF16B602FFC1FD07B1BAFCD9FF7F" box="[668,838,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="37">P. kirkspriggsi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 1.0x in 
<emphasis id="B935FF16B602FFC1FC44B1BAFBCFFF7F" box="[991,1104,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="37">P. s c u r ro r</emphasis>
) and M 
<number id="3D893123B602FFC1FB2FB18AFB23FF78" box="[1204,1212,168,182]" pageId="2" pageNumber="37" value="2.0">2</number>
not reaching wing margin (reaching it in the other two species). The shape of the gonostylus is also characteristic of 
<emphasis id="B935FF16B602FFC1FA9DB1E1FAD7FF12" box="[1286,1352,195,220]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="37">P. w u i</emphasis>
<emphasis id="B935FF16B602FFC1FAC8B1E0FA0AFF12" bold="true" box="[1363,1429,194,220]" pageId="2" pageNumber="37">n. sp.</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
